description: Permanently deletes a  SqlInjectionMatchSet. You can't delete a SqlInjectionMatchSet if it's still used in any Rules or if it still contains any  SqlInjectionMatchTuple objects. If you just want to remove a SqlInjectionMatchSet from a Rule, use  UpdateRule. To permanently delete a SqlInjectionMatchSet from AWS WAF, perform the following steps:

parameters.name: SqlInjectionMatchSetId
parameters.description: The SqlInjectionMatchSetId of the  SqlInjectionMatchSet that you want to delete. SqlInjectionMatchSetId is returned by  CreateSqlInjectionMatchSet and by  ListSqlInjectionMatchSets.

parameters.name: ChangeToken
parameters.description: The value returned by the most recent call to  GetChangeToken.

nested_items.name: ChangeToken
nested_items.description: The ChangeToken that you used to submit the DeleteSqlInjectionMatchSet request. You can also use this value to query the status of the request. For more information, see  GetChangeTokenStatus.
